# Skeleton Loading Patterns

Reference file for the frontend improvement agent. When replacing spinners with skeletons or adding loading states, follow these patterns exactly.

---

## 1. CORE PRINCIPLE

A skeleton is a **low-fidelity preview** of the real content's layout. It must match the real content's dimensions, spacing, and structure so there is **zero layout shift** when data arrives.

**Rules:**
- Skeleton shapes match the real content: text lines are rectangles, avatars are circles, images are rectangles at the correct aspect ratio
- Skeletons use the same padding, gap, and margin as the real content
- Skeletons use the same container dimensions (width, min-height) as the real content
- Never show a skeleton for less than `300ms` — add a minimum delay to prevent flash
- Transition from skeleton to real content with a crossfade — never a hard swap

---

## 2. SHIMMER CSS

The base shimmer animation used by all skeleton elements. Define this once, globally.

```css
@keyframes shimmer {
  0% {
    background-position: -200% 0;
  }
  100% {
    background-position: 200% 0;
  }
}

.skeleton {
  background: linear-gradient(
    90deg,
    var(--color-bg-muted) 25%,
    var(--color-bg-subtle) 50%,
    var(--color-bg-muted) 75%
  );
  background-size: 200% 100%;
  animation: shimmer 1.5s ease-in-out infinite;
  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
}

/* Respect reduced motion preference */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .skeleton {
    animation: none;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
  }
}
```

**As a React component:**
```tsx
interface SkeletonProps {
  width?: string | number;
  height?: string | number;
  borderRadius?: string;
  className?: string;
  style?: React.CSSProperties;
}

function Skeleton({
  width = '100%',
  height = '1rem',
  borderRadius = 'var(--radius-sm)',
  className,
  style,
}: SkeletonProps) {
  return (
    <div
      className={`skeleton ${className ?? ''}`}
      aria-hidden="true"
      style={{
        width,
        height,
        borderRadius,
        ...style,
      }}
    />
  );
}
```

**Key:** Always add `aria-hidden="true"` — skeletons are visual-only, screen readers should ignore them.

