## 5. WHEN TO USE SPINNERS (the exceptions)

Spinners are acceptable ONLY for:
- **Button loading state**: spinner replaces label text, button dimensions stay identical
- **Inline save/submit**: small spinner next to or inside the trigger element
- **Infinite scroll loading indicator**: small spinner at the bottom of a list

```tsx
function LoadingButton({ isLoading, children, ...props }: ButtonProps & { isLoading: boolean }) {
  return (
    <button {...props} disabled={isLoading || props.disabled}>
      {isLoading ? (
        <span
          className="spinner"
          style={{ width: '16px', height: '16px' }}
          aria-label="Loading"
          role="status"
        />
      ) : (
        children
      )}
    </button>
  );
}
```

**Spinner CSS (for the exceptions only):**
```css
.spinner {
  display: inline-block;
  border: 2px solid var(--color-border);
  border-top-color: var(--color-brand);
  border-radius: var(--radius-full);
  animation: spin 0.6s linear infinite;
}

@keyframes spin {
  to { transform: rotate(360deg); }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .spinner {
    animation-duration: 1.5s;
  }
}
```
